00:12:40,994 --> 00:12:45,597
   -That is a defensive wall.   

102
00:12:45,599 --> 00:12:47,599
       Come, I show you.        

103
00:12:51,772 --> 00:12:56,975
 In 1443, Vlad Dracula raised a  
   large army of peasants to    

104
00:12:56,977 --> 00:12:58,777
  defend all of Transylvania.   

105
00:12:58,779 --> 00:13:01,913
  While they fought the Turks   
     in a huge battle near      

106
00:13:01,915 --> 00:13:03,081
          [inaudible].          

107
00:13:03,083 --> 00:13:07,318
      This region suffered      
        a savage attack.        

108
00:13:07,320 --> 00:13:11,122
   The survivors held out as    
      long as they could.       

109
00:13:11,124 --> 00:13:15,460
     Soon, the food and the     
         water ran out.         

110
00:13:15,462 --> 00:13:19,330
  -I read a translation of one  
   of the survivor's diaries.   

111
00:13:19,332 --> 00:13:21,733
 -Then you know what happened.  

112
00:13:21,735 --> 00:13:24,636
 -There were less than 100 left 
     alive in the fortress.     

113
00:13:24,638 --> 00:13:28,239
   -They were waiting to die,   
      but no one attacked.      

114
00:13:28,241 --> 00:13:32,110
 Finally, some brave souls went 
     outside the fortress.      

115
00:13:32,112 --> 00:13:35,213
   They found many dead Turks   
      with bloody throats.      

116
00:13:35,215 --> 00:13:38,016
     The rest had run away.     

117
00:13:38,018 --> 00:13:40,418
  The peasants believed it was  
     the work of vampires.      

118
00:13:42,989 --> 00:13:44,856
         -And still do.         

119
00:13:44,858 --> 00:13:47,659
  Three nights from now is the  
 festival which celebrates the  

120
00:13:47,661 --> 00:13:51,129
    night the vampires saved    
     the people of Prejmer.     

121
00:13:51,131 --> 00:13:52,664
       [mouse squeaking]        

122
00:13:52,666 --> 00:13:54,232
     -Hey, what's up there?     

123
00:13:54,234 --> 00:13:56,534
KARL: Nothing, just 
     an old storage space.      

124
00:13:56,536 --> 00:13:57,202
           -Oh, cool.           

125
00:13:57,204 --> 00:13:58,369
      Let's check it out.       

126
00:13:58,371 --> 00:14:00,071
      -No, the stairs are       
        old and rotten.         

127
00:14:00,073 --> 00:14:01,472
       -I'll be careful.        

128
00:14:17,224 --> 00:14:18,423
              Wow.              

129
00:14:20,293 --> 00:14:23,461
  -The monks who occupied this  
  place were well prepared for  

130
00:14:23,463 --> 00:14:26,197
         the afterlife.         

131
00:14:26,199 --> 00:14:27,098
             Come.              

132
00:14:27,100 --> 00:14:28,499
         There's food.          

133
00:14:38,912 --> 00:14:40,578
          -Mm, great.           

134
00:14:40,580 --> 00:14:41,779
         I'm starving.          

135
00:14:49,789 --> 00:14:51,189
     -[speaking romanian].      

136
00:14:53,293 --> 00:14:54,893
 -Are we the only guests here?  

137
00:14:54,895 --> 00:14:56,427
      Besides the ghosts?       

138
00:14:56,429 --> 00:14:58,663
  -There is one other scholar   
  staying here at the moment.   

139
00:14:58,665 --> 00:15:00,398
    -Oh, another folklorist?    

140
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:02,233
         -A zoologist.          

141
00:15:02,235 --> 00:15:04,602
      But I doubt you will      
        see much of him.        

142
00:15:04,604 --> 00:15:06,738
    He's busy with his work.    

143
00:15:06,740 --> 00:15:11,609
If you'll excuse me, I will get 
    the rest of your things.    

144
00:15:11,611 --> 00:15:13,177
         -[inaudible].          

145
00:15:13,179 --> 00:15:14,545
              Hmm.              

146
00:15:14,547 --> 00:15:17,882
   -Here's toasting Prejmer.    

147
00:15:17,884 --> 00:15:19,050
     May we all publish our     

148
00:15:19,052 --> 00:15:22,754
dissertations and get our PhDs. 

149
00:15:22,756 --> 00:15:24,022
      -Is there any white?      

150
00:15:24,024 --> 00:15:26,858
    -Oh, in Transylvania the    
       best wine is red--       

151
00:15:26,860 --> 00:15:28,259
           blood red.           

152
00:15:45,278 --> 00:15:46,678
    RADU: Bring     
       me the bloodstone.       

153
00:16:46,206 --> 00:16:47,772
     MICHELLE:      
      This is incredible.       

154
00:16:47,774 --> 00:16:49,240
            -Mm-hm.             

155
00:16:49,242 --> 00:16:52,810
 According to the legend, this  
    was a place inhabited by    

156
00:16:52,812 --> 00:16:54,746
 vampires in the 14th century.  

157
00:17:06,493 --> 00:17:07,692
     -[speaking romanian].      

158
00:17:47,767 --> 00:17:48,533
              -OK.              

159
00:17:48,535 --> 00:17:52,737
        One, two, three.        

160
00:17:52,739 --> 00:17:54,205
      Hope this comes out.      

161
00:17:54,207 --> 00:17:55,640
  There's barely enough light.  

162
