00:19:32,172 --> 00:19:35,173
      We'd better get back      
        and wash it off.        

180
00:19:35,175 --> 00:19:36,340
            Come on.            

181
00:20:19,018 --> 00:20:20,017
           -Hi, guys.           

182
00:20:20,019 --> 00:20:21,619
       -How is your room?       

183
00:20:21,621 --> 00:20:23,187
     -I think it'll be OK.      

184
00:20:27,026 --> 00:20:28,793
          What's this?          

185
00:20:28,795 --> 00:20:30,528
MICHELLE: Well, you 
    know, I've been thinking    

186
00:20:30,530 --> 00:20:33,331
   about what Mara said this    
  afternoon, about no one ever  

187
00:20:33,333 --> 00:20:35,433
  mentioning Castle Vladislas.  

188
00:20:35,435 --> 00:20:37,168
       And I went through       
         all my notes.          

189
00:20:37,170 --> 00:20:39,136
 I even looked at the index of  
   all the stuff that's been    

190
00:20:39,138 --> 00:20:41,405
  published about this region   
        over the years.         

191
00:20:41,407 --> 00:20:43,874
 Not one mention of the castle. 

192
00:20:43,876 --> 00:20:45,409
      -Strange, isn't it?       

193
00:20:45,411 --> 00:20:47,478
     -Well, it just doesn't     
          make sense.           

194
00:20:47,480 --> 00:20:50,581
  How can something as old and  
 imposing as that castle not be 

195
00:20:50,583 --> 00:20:52,416
    part of the local lore?     

196
00:20:52,418 --> 00:20:54,385
  -Maybe even something that's  
   been here as long as that    

197
00:20:54,387 --> 00:20:56,787
    castle becomes invisible    
         to all but the         

198
00:20:56,789 --> 00:20:58,189
      most sensitive eyes.      

199
00:21:03,263 --> 00:21:04,795
 Pardon me if I frightened you. 

200
00:21:04,797 --> 00:21:06,397
   My name is Stefan Belescu.   

201
00:21:06,399 --> 00:21:09,900
    -Oh, the zoologist Karl     
         told us about.         

202
00:21:09,902 --> 00:21:12,036
             -Yes.              

203
00:21:12,038 --> 00:21:13,771
         -I'm Lillian.          

204
00:21:13,773 --> 00:21:15,039
        That's Mara, and        
        the hardworking         

205
00:21:15,041 --> 00:21:17,842
   scholar here is Michelle.    

206
00:21:17,844 --> 00:21:20,578
 -I thought I should introduce  
 myself so you won't be alarmed 

