        of the vampires.        

247
00:24:06,345 --> 00:24:12,650
    And since that time, no     
       one in Prejmer has       

248
00:24:12,652 --> 00:24:15,553
   been bitten by a vampire.    

249
00:24:15,555 --> 00:24:18,756
   -You think there are still   
         vampires here?         

250
00:24:18,758 --> 00:24:21,892
      -Vampire do not die.      

251
00:24:21,894 --> 00:24:25,396
      They live for many,       
        many centuries.         

252
00:24:25,398 --> 00:24:29,733
  -And you believe they still   
      sleep in the ruins?       

253
00:24:29,735 --> 00:24:32,002
   -Stay away from the ruins.   

254
00:24:32,004 --> 00:24:33,938
           Stay away.           

255
00:24:33,940 --> 00:24:37,308
    You might interfere with    
      the way things are.       

256
00:24:40,680 --> 00:24:42,179
   -Well, what do you think?    

257
00:24:42,181 --> 00:24:44,582
     Think vampires really      
          sleep here?           

258
00:24:44,584 --> 00:24:46,016
        -Don't be silly.        

259
00:24:46,018 --> 00:24:48,619
  The peasants here have such   
     colorful imaginations.     

260
00:24:48,621 --> 00:24:52,223
    -I don't care if Dracula    
      himself sleeps here.      

261
00:24:52,225 --> 00:24:53,724
  I'm not going another step.   

262
00:25:00,566 --> 00:25:02,533
   -Strange story, isn't it?    

263
00:25:02,535 --> 00:25:05,736
     The stone which drips      
      the blood of saints.      

264
00:25:05,738 --> 00:25:09,273
  -Yeah, there's a fascinating  
   story cycle going on here.   

265
00:25:09,275 --> 00:25:10,908
       First the peasants       
         can't explain          

266
00:25:10,910 --> 00:25:12,443
   what killed the invaders.    

267
00:25:12,445 --> 00:25:15,279
  Maybe it was food poisoning   
   or some disease, something   

268
00:25:15,281 --> 00:25:17,915
      15th-century people       
       didn't understand.       

269
00:25:17,917 --> 00:25:20,451
       Lillian, do you--        

270
00:25:20,453 --> 00:25:22,186
         oh, poor baby.         

271
00:25:22,188 --> 00:25:24,355
    She must be coming down     
        with something.         

272
00:25:28,427 --> 00:25:33,097
MARA: This place has
   an eerie feeling about it.   

273
00:25:33,099 --> 00:25:34,665
     Does it frighten you?      

274
00:25:34,667 --> 00:25:36,200
              -No.              

275
00:25:36,202 --> 00:25:38,369
 We're probably safer here than 
     any city in America--      

276
00:25:40,773 --> 00:25:43,874
 as long as we get out of here  
  before the sun goes down and  

277
00:25:43,876 --> 00:25:46,377
     the vampires wake up.      

278
00:26:51,777 --> 00:26:53,711
             Mara!              

279
00:26:53,713 --> 00:26:54,345
            Lillian!            

280
00:26:54,347 --> 00:26:55,145
            Wake up.            

281
00:26:55,147 --> 00:26:57,081
      We have to get back.      

282
00:26:57,083 --> 00:26:58,515
       -What time is it?        

283
00:26:58,517 --> 00:26:59,283
          -Oh, my God.          

284
00:26:59,285 --> 00:27:01,185
   We've slept for two hours.   

285
00:27:01,187 --> 00:27:03,721
  -Come on, before it gets too  
     dark to find the way.      

286
00:27:03,723 --> 00:27:04,989
         -Don't worry.          

287
00:27:04,991 --> 00:27:06,590
     We'll take a shortcut      
       through the woods.       

288
00:27:06,592 --> 00:27:08,592
        [music playing]         

289
00:28:13,159 --> 00:28:14,958
            -Listen.            

290
00:28:14,960 --> 00:28:17,227
       Did you hear that?       

291
00:28:28,340 --> 00:28:31,542
       -Oh, it's probably       
        just an animal.         

292
00:28:31,544 --> 00:28:33,510
        Don't you think?        

293
00:28:57,336 --> 00:28:58,302
        -It's all right.        

294
00:28:58,304 --> 00:28:59,503
            -Stefan.            

295
00:29:01,607 --> 00:29:03,240
        -You scared this        
        shit out of us!         

296
00:29:03,242 --> 00:29:04,775
      -We were lost and we      
        thought we heard        

297
00:29:04,777 --> 00:29:07,344
     somebody following us.     

298
00:29:07,346 --> 00:29:10,147
     -But you're all right      
           now, yes?            

299
00:29:10,149 --> 00:29:11,949
             -Yes.              

300
00:29:11,951 --> 00:29:12,916
          -All right.           

301
00:29:12,918 --> 00:29:13,951
   I'm going to the fortress.   

302
00:29:13,953 --> 00:29:15,552
 Come back with me, all right?  

303
00:29:15,554 --> 00:29:17,554
        [music playing]         

304
00:30:06,739 --> 00:30:07,704
            Father.             

305
00:30:07,706 --> 00:30:09,706
        [music playing]         

306
00:30:40,239 --> 00:30:43,807
   -Such a touching tableau.    

307
00:30:47,446 --> 00:30:52,482
   Your pain, little brother,   
      makes me feel sick.       

308
00:30:55,254 --> 00:30:59,223
      It's such a mockery       
       of human feelings.       

309
00:31:05,497 --> 00:31:07,164
     Our father was a fool.     

310
00:31:10,469 --> 00:31:11,969
          So are you.           

311
00:31:11,971 --> 00:31:14,137
        [music playing]         

312
00:33:17,062 --> 00:33:19,262
       [knocking on door]       

313
00:33:29,241 --> 00:33:30,440
            -Stefan.            

314
00:33:33,612 --> 00:33:34,811
       -The king is dead.       

315
00:33:37,616 --> 00:33:40,017
             -Radu.             

316
00:33:40,019 --> 00:33:42,219
        [music playing]         

317
00:34:28,867 --> 00:34:30,834
   [DOOR OPENING AND RUNNING    
           FOOTSTEPS]           

318
00:34:30,836 --> 00:34:33,036
        [music playing]         

319
00:35:47,679 --> 00:35:50,180
      -Here it is, Stefan.      

320
00:35:50,182 --> 00:35:51,915
   This what you looking for?   

321
00:35:51,917 --> 00:35:54,084
        [music playing]         

322
00:36:05,697 --> 00:36:07,264
    -Feeling weak, brother?     

323
00:36:07,266 --> 00:36:11,501
     Don't you realize that     
       the sun is rising?       

324
00:36:11,503 --> 00:36:17,073
  You too far from your crypt   
        to make it back.        

325
00:36:17,075 --> 00:36:21,211
    That's what you get for     
   pretending you are human.    

326
00:36:24,716 --> 00:36:30,887
I'm taking the castle and those 
    three little beauties as    

327
00:36:30,889 --> 00:36:32,856
          my consorts.          

328
00:36:32,858 --> 00:36:41,598
 Tell me, Stefan, is there one  
 you like more than the others? 

329
00:36:41,600 --> 00:36:46,770
    I'll make sure to treat     
     her with special care.     

330
00:36:46,772 --> 00:36:48,772
        [music playing]         

331
00:37:11,630 --> 00:37:14,030
            -Stefan.            

332
00:37:14,032 --> 00:37:16,333
      STEFAN:       
       Follow him, Karl.        

333
00:37:16,335 --> 00:37:17,601
        Find his crypt.         

334
00:37:17,603 --> 00:37:19,536
   -There is no time, Stefan.   

335
00:37:19,538 --> 00:37:20,670
       You must help me.        

336
00:37:20,672 --> 00:37:22,439
         Try to get up.         

337
00:37:22,441 --> 00:37:24,441
        [music playing]         

338
00:37:36,421 --> 00:37:38,221
       -You must find it.       

339
00:37:38,223 --> 00:37:41,024
  Find his, his resting place.  

340
00:37:44,830 --> 00:37:47,030
        [music playing]         

341
00:38:42,721 --> 00:38:45,121
     -[speaking romanian].      

342
00:38:45,123 --> 00:38:48,058
   -Doctor asks if you suffer   
          from anemia?          

343
00:38:48,060 --> 00:38:49,459
          -No, never.           

344
00:38:52,531 --> 00:38:53,730
     -[speaking romanian].      

345
00:39:18,857 --> 00:39:21,458
    -He wants to known when     
       you cut your arm.        

346
00:39:21,460 --> 00:39:22,625
      -Yesterday, I think.      

347
00:39:22,627 --> 00:39:23,793
        -The day before.        

348
00:39:23,795 --> 00:39:25,061
              MARA              
[speaking romanian]. 

349
00:39:26,732 --> 00:39:29,366
     -[speaking romanian].      

350
00:39:29,368 --> 00:39:32,502
   -He thinks maybe you lost    
        a lot of blood.         

351
00:39:32,504 --> 00:39:33,069
         -Get serious.          

352
00:39:33,071 --> 00:39:34,471
        It's a scratch.         

353
00:39:40,445 --> 00:39:42,145
     -[speaking romanian].      

354
00:39:42,147 --> 00:39:46,783
  -Take this medicine and stay  
    in bed another 24 hours.    

355
00:39:46,785 --> 00:39:48,184
     -[speaking romanian].      

356
00:39:52,057 --> 00:39:53,456
     -[speaking romanian].      

357
00:40:02,033 --> 00:40:03,433
     -[speaking romanian].      

358
00:40:09,441 --> 00:40:14,310
   -Well, I guess this means    
      the festival's out.       

359
00:40:14,312 --> 00:40:16,346
   -You can't miss it because   
          I can't go.           

360
00:40:16,348 --> 00:40:18,915
      It's the high point       
        of our research.        

361
00:40:18,917 --> 00:40:21,117
   -We can't leave her alone.   

362
00:40:21,119 --> 00:40:22,585
         Yeah, you can.         

363
00:40:22,587 --> 00:40:23,787
          I'll be OK.           

364
00:40:25,957 --> 00:40:29,225
 -Stakes cut from ancient oak.  

365
00:40:32,297 --> 00:40:38,535
    Spear carved from heart     
      of blackthorn tree.       

366
00:40:38,537 --> 00:40:43,139
     And this, for chopping     
         off his head.          

367
00:40:43,141 --> 00:40:46,743
       -You've prepared.        

368
00:40:46,745 --> 00:40:49,145
   You hoped he would return.   

369
00:40:49,147 --> 00:40:51,181
      -You and your father      
       should have killed       

370
00:40:51,183 --> 00:40:52,582
      him a long time ago.      

371
00:40:55,353 --> 00:41:03,893
   I would have destroyed him   
   myself, but I was afraid.    

372
00:41:03,895 --> 00:41:05,695
    I could never get close     
       enough to drive a        

373
00:41:05,697 --> 00:41:08,832
    stake through his heart.    

374
00:41:08,834 --> 00:41:11,434
   But I can get close enough   
         to shoot him.          

375
00:41:14,206 --> 00:41:17,106
  -Karl, lead won't stop him.   

376
00:41:17,108 --> 00:41:18,741
   He'll laugh in your face.    

377
00:41:18,743 --> 00:41:19,509
             -Lead?             

378
00:41:19,511 --> 00:41:20,677
              No.               

379
00:41:20,679 --> 00:41:22,946
      I have another idea.      

380
00:41:22,948 --> 00:41:24,514
        [music playing]         

381
00:41:33,625 --> 00:41:34,757
         -Rosary beads.         

382
00:41:34,759 --> 00:41:36,726
 KARL: Cut of wood. 

383
00:41:36,728 --> 00:41:39,062
          Holy relics.          

384
00:41:39,064 --> 00:41:41,097
      That is what I will       
        shoot him with,         

385
00:41:41,099 --> 00:41:43,433
  straight through the heart.   

386
00:41:43,435 --> 00:41:46,269
      -I'll watch over the      
       girls until dawn.        

387
00:41:46,271 --> 00:41:48,972
  Can you make sure they leave  
  by tomorrow without telling   

388
00:41:48,974 --> 00:41:50,406
        them the truth?         

389
00:41:50,408 --> 00:41:51,641
          -I can try.           

390
00:41:51,643 --> 00:41:59,282
  -They mustn't know anything,  
      especially about me.      

391
00:41:59,284 --> 00:42:02,151
     KARL: You      
      are falling in love.      

392
00:42:02,153 --> 00:42:05,121
       -Don't be foolish.       

393
00:42:05,123 --> 00:42:07,790
   -The way you look at her--   

394
00:42:07,792 --> 00:42:10,960
it is you who are foolish if you
   think you can fall in love   

395
00:42:10,962 --> 00:42:13,796
      with a mortal woman.      

396
00:42:13,798 --> 00:42:15,365
       -She's different.        

397
00:42:15,367 --> 00:42:17,867
        -From you, yes.         

398
00:42:17,869 --> 00:42:20,203
  She will die, you will live.  

399
00:42:20,205 --> 00:42:22,438
       Why do you want to       
         take the risk?         

400
00:42:25,744 --> 00:42:31,147
  -When I look at her, when I   
    look into her eyes, I--     

401
00:42:31,149 --> 00:42:32,549
      there's this light.       

402
00:42:36,621 --> 00:42:38,288
    She makes me want again.    

403
00:42:38,290 --> 00:42:40,456
  -She has your mother's eyes.  

404
00:42:43,461 --> 00:42:44,661
             -Yes.              

405
00:42:48,800 --> 00:42:50,800
        [music playing]         

406
00:43:19,731 --> 00:43:23,700
  -This festival is based on a  
    very strange old custom.    

407
00:43:23,702 --> 00:43:26,669
 The peasants used to believe-- 
    and many still do-- that    

408
00:43:26,671 --> 00:43:32,342
  sickness and misfortune are   
 caused by ghosts, the undead.  

409
00:43:32,344 --> 00:43:34,811
 Hey, stop looking for Stefan.  

410
00:43:34,813 --> 00:43:36,245
  Keep your mind on your work.  

411
00:44:09,514 --> 00:44:12,315
   -To cure the illness that    
   plagued the village, they    

412
00:44:12,317 --> 00:44:14,751
 brought a white horse through  
 the cemetery and made it jump  

413
00:44:14,753 --> 00:44:16,653
     over the fresh graves.     

414
00:44:16,655 --> 00:44:20,690
  If the horse refused to jump  
  over a grave, there lay one   

415
00:44:20,692 --> 00:44:22,091
        who was undead.         

416
00:45:08,540 --> 00:45:13,609
  They will unearth the grave,  
   break open the coffin, and   

417
00:45:13,611 --> 00:45:16,045
   drive a stake through the    
      heart of the undead.      

418
00:45:18,283 --> 00:45:25,388
 Then they take the heart from  
     the body and boil it.      

419
00:45:25,390 --> 00:45:29,726
    Everyone will drink from    
      that water, and the       

420
00:45:29,728 --> 00:45:32,729
     illness will be cured.     

421
00:45:32,731 --> 00:45:36,332
   -A barbaric custom handed    
    down from ancient times.    

422
00:45:36,334 --> 00:45:38,668
            -Stefan.            

423
00:45:38,670 --> 00:45:39,869
   -What are you doing here?    

424
00:45:39,871 --> 00:45:41,771
     You should be watching     
         over Lillian.          

425
00:45:41,773 --> 00:45:44,474
  -Well, this is an important   
     part of our research.      

426
00:45:44,476 --> 00:45:46,642
     -Speaking of research,     
      give me the camera.       

427
00:45:46,644 --> 00:45:48,578
  I want to make some photos.   

428
00:45:48,580 --> 00:45:50,546
        [music playing]         

429
00:46:10,435 --> 00:46:11,634
     -Stefan, what's wrong?     

430
00:46:15,406 --> 00:46:18,407
      -I'm afraid for you.      

431
00:46:18,409 --> 00:46:21,210
      You're so beautiful.      

432
00:46:21,212 --> 00:46:24,180
      This can be such a--      
      such a cruel place.       

433
00:46:24,182 --> 00:46:25,782
   If anything should happen.   

434
00:46:25,784 --> 00:46:27,784
        [music playing]         

435
00:47:01,586 --> 00:47:02,418
              -I--              

436
00:47:02,420 --> 00:47:03,953
       I must leave now.        

437
00:47:03,955 --> 00:47:06,155
        [music playing]         

438
00:47:22,507 --> 00:47:23,606
             -Mara.             

439
00:47:23,608 --> 00:47:25,875
  -Hey, what's wrong with you?  

440
00:47:25,877 --> 00:47:27,844
  -I've got a strange feeling.  

441
00:47:27,846 --> 00:47:30,513
     I want to go and check     
          on Lillian.           

442
00:47:30,515 --> 00:47:33,683
  -Is it Lillian you've got a   
 strange feeling for or Stefan? 

443
00:47:33,685 --> 00:47:35,051
      -I'm serious, Mara.       

444
00:47:35,053 --> 00:47:37,119
     Can I take the car and     
       I'll come back and       

445
00:47:37,121 --> 00:47:38,521
      get you in a while?       

446
00:47:40,992 --> 00:47:42,959
       -You sure you can        
         find your way?         

447
00:47:42,961 --> 00:47:43,960
             -Yeah.             

448
00:47:43,962 --> 00:47:45,394
   -And don't worry about me.   

449
00:47:45,396 --> 00:47:47,597
      I'll get a ride back      
           later, OK?           

450
00:47:47,599 --> 00:47:48,598
              -OK.              

451
00:47:48,600 --> 00:47:50,166
        [music playing]         

452
00:51:00,258 --> 00:51:02,291
     -Tell me what's going      
        on here, Stefan.        

453
00:51:05,596 --> 00:51:06,796
       Tell me the truth.       

454
00:51:09,434 --> 00:51:10,633
            Please?             

455
00:51:13,204 --> 00:51:16,772
       -Centuries ago, my       
       father fell under        

456
00:51:16,774 --> 00:51:19,742
   the spell of a sorceress.    

457
00:51:19,744 --> 00:51:22,711
   She was evil and powerful,   
            and she             

458
00:51:22,713 --> 00:51:26,082
  craved an unusual offspring.  

459
00:51:26,084 --> 00:51:29,785
       Radu is the issue        
         of that union.         

460
00:51:29,787 --> 00:51:33,656
      -But you can't be--       

461
00:51:33,658 --> 00:51:37,193
          -Yes, I can.          

462
00:51:43,334 --> 00:51:46,702
  But I live in the way of my   
   father, at peace with the    

463
00:51:46,704 --> 00:51:48,104
         mortal world.          

464
00:51:51,375 --> 00:51:54,510
In the years following the siege
     of Prejmer, my father      

465
00:51:54,512 --> 00:51:57,012
       fell in love with        
        a mortal woman--        

466
00:51:57,014 --> 00:51:58,414
           my mother.           

467
00:52:02,720 --> 00:52:04,120
 Radu and I are half-brothers.  

468
00:52:07,525 --> 00:52:08,724
       -And your mother?        

469
00:52:11,696 --> 00:52:13,262
        -She died a very        
         long time ago.         

470
00:52:27,678 --> 00:52:29,645
        [music playing]         

471
00:52:41,325 --> 00:52:45,594
  When morning comes you must   
    take her away from here.    

472
00:52:45,596 --> 00:52:48,531
      But what about Mara?      

473
00:52:48,533 --> 00:52:52,401
 -If she's not back by morning, 
 Karl will go into the village  

474
00:52:52,403 --> 00:52:53,135
         and find her.          

475
00:52:53,137 --> 00:52:57,106
    And then you must leave.    

476
00:52:57,108 --> 00:52:58,674
        [music playing]         

477
00:53:16,827 --> 00:53:19,762
   -I must go now and sleep.    

478
00:53:19,764 --> 00:53:22,364
      Sun will be up soon.      

479
00:53:22,366 --> 00:53:24,333
        [music playing]         

480
00:53:50,294 --> 00:53:54,163
 -What are you going to do now? 

481
00:53:54,165 --> 00:53:55,764
      -I must destroy him.      

482
00:53:59,737 --> 00:54:01,637
      -I want to help you.      

483
00:54:01,639 --> 00:54:03,405
        -You leave here.        

484
00:54:03,407 --> 00:54:05,641
    As soon as the sun is up    
       you leave here and       

485
00:54:05,643 --> 00:54:07,042
      you never look back.      

486
00:54:09,280 --> 00:54:11,080
  That is how you can help me.  

487
00:54:44,849 --> 00:54:47,449
 -I must leave you now, my pet. 

488
00:54:51,255 --> 00:54:55,257
     But my little friends      
         will keep you          

489
00:54:55,259 --> 00:54:58,460
     company until tonight.     

490
00:54:58,462 --> 00:55:00,396
        [music playing]         

491
00:56:04,295 --> 00:56:05,494
        -It's too late.         

492
00:56:08,666 --> 00:56:10,065
           -Dear God.           

493
00:56:12,570 --> 00:56:14,737
     I could not find Mara.     

494
00:56:14,739 --> 00:56:16,672
   The villagers are afraid.    

495
00:56:16,674 --> 00:56:20,209
